WEBVTT

00:00:32.930 --> 00:00:41.560
(boat crashing against waves)

00:00:41.560 --> 00:00:42.230
♪

00:00:42.230 --> 00:00:43.030
>> Narrator: POLAR EXPLORERS

00:00:43.030 --> 00:00:44.330
HAVE AN UNPARALLELED WINDOW

00:00:44.330 --> 00:00:45.230
ON THE WORKINGS OF OUR

00:00:45.230 --> 00:00:49.000
PLANET.

00:00:49.000 --> 00:00:50.230
RESEARCH IN THE POLAR REGIONS

00:00:50.230 --> 00:00:51.730
REVEALED THE MECHANISMS OF

00:00:51.730 --> 00:00:54.360
THE EARTH'S MAGNETIC FIELD,

00:00:54.360 --> 00:00:55.230
THE PROPERTIES OF THE UPPER

00:00:55.230 --> 00:00:56.960
ATMOSPHERE, AND THE EXISTENCE

00:00:56.960 --> 00:00:58.200
OF THE HOLE IN THE OZONE

00:00:58.200 --> 00:01:00.860
LAYER.

00:01:02.460 --> 00:01:04.260
IN ANTARCTICA, CLAUDE LORIUS

00:01:04.260 --> 00:01:05.560
MADE A DISCOVERY THAT ROCKED

00:01:05.560 --> 00:01:07.330
THE WORLD.

00:01:07.330 --> 00:01:08.260
HE CONCLUSIVELY PROVED THE

00:01:08.260 --> 00:01:11.430
EXISTENCE OF GLOBAL WARMING.

00:01:11.430 --> 00:01:13.100
TODAY, HE'S RETURNED TO THE

00:01:13.100 --> 00:01:14.360
CONTINENT TO RECOVER THE

00:01:14.360 --> 00:01:15.660
MEMORY THAT HE LOST IN AN

00:01:15.660 --> 00:01:19.030
ACCIDENT.

00:01:33.100 --> 00:01:46.930
♪

00:01:46.930 --> 00:01:48.230
>> Narrator: CURIOUSLY, IT

00:01:48.230 --> 00:01:49.360
WAS THE SCIENTIFIC KNOWLEDGE

00:01:49.360 --> 00:01:51.960
THAT CAME BACK FIRST.

00:01:51.960 --> 00:01:53.100
BUT TO REGAIN THE FULL MEMORY

00:01:53.100 --> 00:01:54.430
OF HIS LIFE WITH ALL ITS

00:01:54.430 --> 00:01:56.260
EXPERIENCES HE HAD TO RETRACE

00:01:56.260 --> 00:01:57.460
THE STEPS OF HIS PAST

00:01:57.460 --> 00:02:00.700
EXPEDITIONS.

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:33.030
>> Narrator: FOR LORIUS, THE

00:02:33.030 --> 00:02:35.900
ADVENTURE BEGAN IN 1957.

00:02:35.900 --> 00:02:36.900
HAVING FINISHED HIS PHYSICAL

00:02:36.900 --> 00:02:38.730
SCIENCE STUDIES HE APPLIED TO

00:02:38.730 --> 00:02:40.030
SPEND A YEAR IN A NEWLY BUILT

00:02:40.030 --> 00:02:41.230
SCIENTIFIC BASE IN

00:02:41.230 --> 00:02:45.630
ANTARCTICA, THE CHARCOT BASE.

00:03:03.760 --> 00:03:07.460
♪

00:03:18.230 --> 00:03:23.960
♪

00:03:23.960 --> 00:03:24.730
>> Narrator: DURING THIS

00:03:24.730 --> 00:03:26.000
EXPEDITION, LORIUS WROTE THE

00:03:26.000 --> 00:03:27.330
FIRST OF THE JOURNALS THAT

00:03:27.330 --> 00:03:28.500
WOULD ACCOMPANY HIM

00:03:28.500 --> 00:03:29.500
THROUGHOUT HIS ASTONISHING

00:03:29.500 --> 00:03:31.900
JOURNEY.

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:50.600
(winds blowing)

00:03:50.600 --> 00:03:51.430
>> Narrator: SCIENTISTS

00:03:51.430 --> 00:03:52.460
STARTED TO BECOME INTERESTED

00:03:52.460 --> 00:03:55.800
IN THE POLES IN THE 1950'S.

00:03:55.800 --> 00:03:56.930
THE CHARCOT BASE WAS SET UP

00:03:56.930 --> 00:03:58.000
TO UNDERSTAND THE INFLUENCE

00:03:58.000 --> 00:03:59.330
OF THE ANTARCTIC ON THE

00:03:59.330 --> 00:04:01.000
EARTH'S CLIMATE, AND TO

00:04:01.000 --> 00:04:03.260
MEASURE POLAR MAGNETISM.

00:04:03.260 --> 00:04:10.500
(sounds of machinery)

00:04:26.800 --> 00:04:36.430
(winds blowing)

00:04:36.430 --> 00:04:37.130
>> Narrator: THREE PEOPLE

00:04:37.130 --> 00:04:37.960
WOULD ATTEMPT TO SPEND

00:04:37.960 --> 00:04:39.730
THE WINTER AT THE SOUTH POLE,

00:04:39.730 --> 00:04:40.900
STAYING ONE YEAR CUT

00:04:40.900 --> 00:04:42.030
OFF FROM THE WORLD,

00:04:42.030 --> 00:04:43.960
SURROUNDED BY ICE, JACQUES

00:04:43.960 --> 00:04:45.660
DUBOIS, AN ENGINEER, AND THE

00:04:45.660 --> 00:04:46.660
ONLY PERSON WITH POLAR

00:04:46.660 --> 00:04:49.230
EXPERIENCE, CLAUDE LORIUS,

00:04:49.230 --> 00:04:50.430
AND A YOUNG PHYSICIST

00:04:50.430 --> 00:04:52.800
ROLAND SCHLICH.

00:04:52.800 --> 00:04:53.900
THEIR FIRST TASK WAS TO DIG

00:04:53.900 --> 00:04:55.500
TUNNELS FOR BASIC SURVIVAL

00:04:55.500 --> 00:04:56.400
AND TO INSTALL THE

00:04:56.400 --> 00:04:58.760
LABORATORIES.

00:05:14.930 --> 00:05:27.460
(winds blowing)

00:05:27.460 --> 00:05:28.160
>> Narrator: A WINDMILL AT

00:05:28.160 --> 00:05:29.030
THE CENTER OF THE BASE

00:05:29.030 --> 00:05:33.960
PROVIDED ENERGY.

00:05:33.960 --> 00:05:35.400
NEXT TO IT, A METEOROLOGICAL

00:05:35.400 --> 00:05:36.830
OBSERVATION TOWER MEASURED

00:05:36.830 --> 00:05:37.830
THE TEMPERATURE AND THE

00:05:37.830 --> 00:05:41.630
WIND SPEED.

00:05:41.630 --> 00:05:42.530
EVERYTHING WAS IN PLACE FOR

00:05:42.530 --> 00:05:43.460
THE TEAM TO START THEIR

00:05:43.460 --> 00:05:46.000
EXPERIMENTS.

00:06:30.560 --> 00:06:31.460
>> Narrator: POLAR WINTER

00:06:31.460 --> 00:06:32.400
CAME TO THE BASE, BRINGING

00:06:32.400 --> 00:06:33.830
WITH IT VIOLENT STORMS THAT

00:06:33.830 --> 00:06:35.000
DESTROYED ALL EXTERNAL

00:06:35.000 --> 00:06:36.760
EQUIPMENT, DEPRIVING THE BASE

00:06:36.760 --> 00:06:38.400
OF RADIO CONTACT, THEIR ONLY

00:06:38.400 --> 00:06:39.730
MEANS OF COMMUNICATION

00:06:39.730 --> 00:06:41.260
WITH DUMONT D'URVILLE AND

00:06:41.260 --> 00:06:43.260
THE WORLD.

00:06:43.260 --> 00:06:44.560
FOR MORE THAN SEVEN WEEKS THE

00:06:44.560 --> 00:06:45.730
THREE MEN COULDN'T EVEN TELL

00:06:45.730 --> 00:06:46.800
THEIR FAMILIES THEY WERE

00:06:46.800 --> 00:06:50.160
STILL ALIVE.

00:06:56.930 --> 00:07:03.330
(radio beeping)

00:07:24.100 --> 00:07:24.830
>> Narrator: LORIUS AND HIS

00:07:24.830 --> 00:07:25.760
COLLEAGUES MANAGED TO

00:07:25.760 --> 00:07:27.000
IMPROVISE A WAY TO PRODUCE A

00:07:27.000 --> 00:07:28.700
SMALL ELECTRIC CURRENT AND

00:07:28.700 --> 00:07:30.060
REASSURE THEIR COLLEAGUES AND

00:07:30.060 --> 00:07:32.130
FAMILIES BY RADIO.

00:07:32.130 --> 00:07:33.000
THEN THEY HAD TO SAVE THE

00:07:33.000 --> 00:07:35.130
SCIENTIFIC PROGRAM.

00:10:25.160 --> 00:10:35.200
♪

00:10:35.200 --> 00:10:40.360
♪

00:10:49.700 --> 00:10:59.730
(machinery engine)

00:10:59.730 --> 00:11:10.730
(machinery engine)

00:11:10.730 --> 00:11:16.060
(people laughing)

00:11:34.000 --> 00:11:44.030
♪

00:11:44.030 --> 00:11:49.230
♪

00:11:59.560 --> 00:12:00.360
>> Narrator: THE EXPERIENCE

00:12:00.360 --> 00:12:01.300
AFFECTED CLAUDE LORIUS

00:12:01.300 --> 00:12:02.930
DEEPLY.

00:12:02.930 --> 00:12:04.900
AT 26, HE REALIZED THAT HIS

00:12:04.900 --> 00:12:06.230
PLACE WAS THERE DESPITE THE

00:12:06.230 --> 00:12:07.560
HARDSHIPS AND EXTREME

00:12:07.560 --> 00:12:10.260
CONDITIONS.

00:12:10.260 --> 00:12:11.330
FROM THIS POINT ON, HE WOULD

00:12:11.330 --> 00:12:12.600
NOT REST UNTIL HE RETURNED TO

00:12:12.600 --> 00:12:14.500
THE SOUTH POLE.

00:12:14.500 --> 00:12:15.860
ANTARCTICA HAD CHANGED HIM

00:12:15.860 --> 00:12:18.200
FOREVER.

00:12:44.660 --> 00:12:45.430
>> Narrator: IT WAS NOVEMBER

00:12:45.430 --> 00:12:47.130
1959.

00:12:47.130 --> 00:12:48.860
THE EXPERIMENT WAS A FIRST, A

00:12:48.860 --> 00:12:51.400
TRIP OF 2,500 KILOMETERS IN

00:12:51.400 --> 00:12:53.630
UNKNOWN TERRITORY.

00:12:53.630 --> 00:12:55.000
FOR FOUR MONTHS, EIGHT MEN OF

00:12:55.000 --> 00:12:56.260
DIFFERENT NATIONALITIES WOULD

00:12:56.260 --> 00:12:59.430
LIVE TOGETHER, CLAUDE LORIUS,

00:12:59.430 --> 00:13:01.760
THE ONLY FRENCHMEN, AN

00:13:01.760 --> 00:13:04.830
AUSTRALIAN, SOME AMERICANS, A

00:13:04.830 --> 00:13:06.260
NEW ZEALANDER, AND A

00:13:06.260 --> 00:13:07.960
DUTCHMEN, FRANS VAN DER

00:13:07.960 --> 00:13:09.430
HOEVEN, THE LEADER OF THE

00:13:09.430 --> 00:13:11.330
EXPEDITION.

00:13:11.330 --> 00:13:13.500
>> ALL OF US REALIZED THAT WE

00:13:13.500 --> 00:13:16.560
WERE IN UNKNOWN TERRITORY

00:13:16.560 --> 00:13:17.830
BECAUSE THAT WAS THE PURPOSE

00:13:17.830 --> 00:13:19.760
OF THE TRIP, TO GO SOMEWHERE

00:13:19.760 --> 00:13:21.160
WHERE NO ONE ELSE HAS BEEN

00:13:21.160 --> 00:13:24.230
BEFORE, AND TO LOOK AROUND

00:13:24.230 --> 00:13:27.500
AND MEASURE WHAT'S THERE.

00:13:27.500 --> 00:13:28.760
BUT I DON'T THINK THAT WAS

00:13:28.760 --> 00:13:31.700
OUR MAIN OBSESSION.

00:13:31.700 --> 00:13:34.200
OUR MAIN OBSESSION WAS THE

00:13:34.200 --> 00:13:36.560
EVERY DAY IRRITATION AND

00:13:36.560 --> 00:13:39.260
EVERY DAY FEAR, HOW ARE WE

00:13:39.260 --> 00:13:43.860
GOING TO GET THROUGH?

00:13:43.860 --> 00:13:44.860
>> Narrator: THE UNHEATED

00:13:44.860 --> 00:13:45.930
VEHICLES WERE THE EXPLORER'S

00:13:45.930 --> 00:13:47.600
ONLY SHELTER, BOTH DURING THE

00:13:47.600 --> 00:13:50.730
DAY AND AT NIGHT.

00:13:50.730 --> 00:13:51.600
WHATEVER THE WEATHER, THE

00:13:51.600 --> 00:13:52.760
CONVOY STOPPED EVERY 50

00:13:52.760 --> 00:13:55.330
KILOMETERS.

00:13:58.060 --> 00:13:59.130
THEY TOOK MEASUREMENTS AND

00:13:59.130 --> 00:14:00.900
SAMPLES, AND SET OFF SMALL

00:14:00.900 --> 00:14:02.200
EXPLOSIONS TO MEASURE THE

00:14:02.200 --> 00:14:05.330
THICKNESS OF THE ICE.

00:14:05.330 --> 00:14:09.730
(explosion)

00:14:09.730 --> 00:14:19.760
(wind blowing)

00:14:19.760 --> 00:14:25.900
(wind blowing)

00:14:25.900 --> 00:14:27.060
THEIR GOAL WAS TO REACH THE

00:14:27.060 --> 00:14:29.260
ICE CAP.

00:14:29.260 --> 00:14:30.360
TO DO THAT, THEY HAD TO CLIMB

00:14:30.360 --> 00:14:33.860
A 100-KILOMETER LONG GLACIER.

00:15:01.200 --> 00:15:02.130
>> Narrator: LORIUS' GROUP

00:15:02.130 --> 00:15:03.030
MANAGED TO AVOID THE

00:15:03.030 --> 00:15:04.300
CREVASSES, BUT A LITTLE

00:15:04.300 --> 00:15:05.800
FURTHER ON ANOTHER TEAM WAS

00:15:05.800 --> 00:15:07.360
LESS FORTUNATE AND LOST

00:15:07.360 --> 00:15:10.800
SEVERAL OF IT'S MEN.

00:15:10.800 --> 00:15:20.830
(wind blowing)

00:15:20.830 --> 00:15:39.460
(wind blowing)

00:15:39.460 --> 00:15:40.730
AT TIMES, BLIZZARDS OBSCURED

00:15:40.730 --> 00:15:42.260
ALL VISIBILITY.

00:15:42.260 --> 00:15:43.430
THEY HAD TO STOP FOR DAYS, OR

00:15:43.430 --> 00:15:45.100
EVEN WEEKS.

00:15:45.100 --> 00:15:46.100
EVERYTHING WAS DICTATED BY

00:15:46.100 --> 00:15:49.630
THE WEATHER.

00:15:50.460 --> 00:15:51.400
>> ANTARCTICA IS NOT A

00:15:51.400 --> 00:15:52.860
PLEASANT ENVIRONMENT.

00:15:52.860 --> 00:15:53.760
IT IS A PUNISHING

00:15:53.760 --> 00:15:57.360
ENVIRONMENT, AND IF YOU ARE

00:15:57.360 --> 00:15:59.030
OUT ON THE PLATEAU YOU NEVER

00:15:59.030 --> 00:16:01.560
FEEL RELAXED.

00:16:01.560 --> 00:16:04.200
YOU CANNOT GO OUT FOR A WALK

00:16:04.200 --> 00:16:06.360
BECAUSE YOU WILL BE

00:16:06.360 --> 00:16:08.330
SUFFERING.

00:16:08.330 --> 00:16:11.160
SLEEPING AT NIGHT IS AN IFFY

00:16:11.160 --> 00:16:14.060
PROPOSITION.

00:17:00.660 --> 00:17:14.230
(wind blowing)

00:17:14.230 --> 00:17:15.000
>> Narrator: THE EVENING MEAL

00:17:15.000 --> 00:17:17.460
WAS A TIME FOR RELAXATION.

00:17:17.460 --> 00:17:18.500
THE COOK, WHO WAS ALSO THE

00:17:18.500 --> 00:17:20.300
TRIP'S PSYCHOLOGIST, WOULD

00:17:20.300 --> 00:17:21.360
DISCREETLY START THE TAPE

00:17:21.360 --> 00:17:23.730
RECORDER.

00:17:23.730 --> 00:17:24.960
HE STUDIED THE SMALL GROUP AS

00:17:24.960 --> 00:17:26.100
THEY ENDURED THE EXTREME

00:17:26.100 --> 00:17:31.600
LIVING CONDITIONS.

00:17:31.600 --> 00:17:32.660
THESE STUDIES WOULD LATER BE

00:17:32.660 --> 00:17:34.030
USED TO UNDERSTAND HOW SPACE

00:17:34.030 --> 00:17:35.700
CREWS FUNCTION AND TO SELECT

00:17:35.700 --> 00:17:39.700
ASTRONAUTS.

00:17:39.700 --> 00:17:46.560
♪

00:17:46.560 --> 00:17:48.460
>> OUR LITTLE CONTRIBUTION TO

00:17:48.460 --> 00:17:50.460
THE ANTARCTIC HISTORY ENDED

00:17:50.460 --> 00:17:53.200
IN 1960, AND AS YOU CAN SEE

00:17:53.200 --> 00:17:54.830
ON THIS MAP THERE ARE SEVERAL

00:17:54.830 --> 00:17:56.360
MOUNTAIN PEAKS THAT HAVE THE

00:17:56.360 --> 00:17:57.730
NAMES OF EXPEDITIONARY

00:17:57.730 --> 00:17:59.230
MEMBERS.

00:17:59.230 --> 00:18:00.430
AND ONE OF THEM IS OF COURSE

00:18:00.430 --> 00:18:01.830
CLAUDE LORIUS, AND ANOTHER IS

00:18:01.830 --> 00:18:04.360
MOUNT VAN DER HOEVEN, IT IS

00:18:04.360 --> 00:18:05.560
MY NAME.

00:18:05.560 --> 00:18:08.300
AND THERE IS A LITTLE PLACE

00:18:08.300 --> 00:18:11.660
THAT HAS THE NAME OF THE

00:18:11.660 --> 00:18:13.560
SNOW CAPS, THE VEHICLES THAT

00:18:13.560 --> 00:18:16.260
WE HAD.

00:18:17.560 --> 00:18:18.530
>> Narrator: THE MOUNTAIN

00:18:18.530 --> 00:18:19.360
RANGES DISCOVERED BY THE

00:18:19.360 --> 00:18:20.530
EXPEDITION PROVED TO BE

00:18:20.530 --> 00:18:22.760
IMPOSSIBLE.

00:18:22.760 --> 00:18:24.100
THE TEAM HAD TO BE EVACUATED

00:18:24.100 --> 00:18:25.530
BY PLANE AND EVERYTHING LEFT

00:18:25.530 --> 00:18:27.060
BEHIND, EXCEPT FOR THE

00:18:27.060 --> 00:18:32.630
PRECIOUS SAMPLES.

00:18:32.630 --> 00:18:33.960
FOR LORIUS, THE EXPEDITION

00:18:33.960 --> 00:18:35.730
HAD BEEN VERY POSITIVE.

00:18:35.730 --> 00:18:37.160
IN THE ANTARCTIC ICE, HE HAD

00:18:37.160 --> 00:18:38.660
FOUND A WAY TO ESTABLISH PAST

00:18:38.660 --> 00:18:40.230
TEMPERATURES.

00:18:40.230 --> 00:18:41.930
A NEW PATH OPENED UP FOR HIM,

00:18:41.930 --> 00:18:42.930
AND ANOTHER MEETING WITH

00:18:42.930 --> 00:18:44.830
JEAN JOUZEL.

00:19:00.800 --> 00:19:01.560
>> Narrator: LORIUS PROVED

00:19:01.560 --> 00:19:02.760
THAT THE PROPORTION OF HEAVY

00:19:02.760 --> 00:19:04.130
HYDROGEN IN THE ICE VARIED

00:19:04.130 --> 00:19:05.760
ACCORDING TO THE TEMPERATURE

00:19:05.760 --> 00:19:08.430
AT THE TIME THE ICE FORMED.

00:19:08.430 --> 00:19:09.660
THIS GAVE SCIENTISTS A NEW

00:19:09.660 --> 00:19:11.630
TOOL, THE ISOTOPIC

00:19:11.630 --> 00:19:13.360
THERMOMETER.

00:19:13.360 --> 00:19:14.560
THANKS TO THIS TOOL, THEY

00:19:14.560 --> 00:19:15.560
COULD ESTABLISH PAST

00:19:15.560 --> 00:19:17.330
TEMPERATURES AT A GIVEN SITE

00:19:17.330 --> 00:19:18.360
JUST FROM TAKING SAMPLES OF

00:19:18.360 --> 00:19:21.460
ICE THERE.

00:19:21.460 --> 00:19:29.330
♪

00:19:29.330 --> 00:19:30.560
FOR LORIUS, THE '60'S LOOKED

00:19:30.560 --> 00:19:32.560
PROMISING.

00:19:32.560 --> 00:19:33.860
HIS INTUITION GRADUALLY LED

00:19:33.860 --> 00:19:35.830
HIM TO ANOTHER DISCOVERY,

00:19:35.830 --> 00:19:37.030
A NEW TOOL TO RECONSTRUCT

00:19:37.030 --> 00:19:38.930
THE CLIMATE OF THE PAST.

00:19:38.930 --> 00:19:40.560
>> WELL, IT'S ON NEW YEAR'S

00:19:40.560 --> 00:19:42.300
DAY, WE WILL REMEMBER THIS,

00:19:42.300 --> 00:19:43.660
TO NEW YEAR'S DAY,

00:19:43.660 --> 00:19:44.930
NOW HAVE A SIP.

00:19:44.930 --> 00:19:50.230
>> THANK YOU.

00:19:50.230 --> 00:19:56.060
ONE OF MY FAVORITE STORIES IN

00:19:56.060 --> 00:19:57.400
THIS IS THAT IS THE FIRST

00:19:57.400 --> 00:19:59.930
TIME WE SAW THAT WE COULD NOT

00:19:59.930 --> 00:20:02.260
ONLY RECONSTRUCT THE CLIMATE

00:20:02.260 --> 00:20:03.860
FROM ICICLES BUT ALSO THE

00:20:03.860 --> 00:20:06.230
COMPOSITION OF THE AIR.

00:20:06.230 --> 00:20:09.230
IT WAS DRINKING.

00:20:09.230 --> 00:20:10.160
>> DRINKING WHISKEY?

00:20:10.160 --> 00:20:11.500
>> A PIECE OF ICE WHICH CAME

00:20:11.500 --> 00:20:14.830
FROM THE CORE, AND WE THOUGHT

00:20:14.830 --> 00:20:20.700
WHY SHOULDN'T WE TRY TO

00:20:20.700 --> 00:20:22.130
PRESERVE A LOT OF THE

00:20:22.130 --> 00:20:24.030
COMPOSITION OF THE ICE.

00:20:24.030 --> 00:20:25.200
>> IS THAT WHERE THAT CAME

00:20:25.200 --> 00:20:26.200
FROM?

00:20:26.200 --> 00:20:27.800
>> YES, BUT IT TOOK, OF

00:20:27.800 --> 00:20:29.260
COURSE AS YOU KNOW, MANY

00:20:29.260 --> 00:20:32.130
YEARS TO PROVE THAT THIS WAS

00:20:32.130 --> 00:20:34.960
THE IDEA.

00:20:34.960 --> 00:20:36.330
>> WHEN I FIRST CAME TO

00:20:36.330 --> 00:20:38.360
ANTARCTICA, GLACIOLOGY WAS

00:20:38.360 --> 00:20:40.630
PROBABLY THE LEAST IMPORTANT

00:20:40.630 --> 00:20:42.200
SUBJECT IT SEEMED.

00:20:42.200 --> 00:20:44.300
>> NO, NO!

00:20:44.300 --> 00:20:45.760
>> WHEN I FIRST CAME, NO

00:20:45.760 --> 00:20:47.160
SERIOUSLY, AND NOW IT'S ONE

00:20:47.160 --> 00:20:48.760
OF THE MOST IMPORTANT.

00:20:48.760 --> 00:20:49.730
>> YES.

00:20:49.730 --> 00:20:50.700
>> YES, BUT SERIOUSLY WHEN I

00:20:50.700 --> 00:20:51.730
FIRST CAME...

00:20:51.730 --> 00:20:52.800
>> I DON'T KNOW HOW LONG IT

00:20:52.800 --> 00:20:55.160
WILL BE LIKE THIS.

00:20:55.160 --> 00:20:56.260
>> BUT OBVIOUSLY IT'S VERY

00:20:56.260 --> 00:20:58.260
IMPORTANT NOW.

00:20:58.260 --> 00:21:01.230
SO IT WAS ALL BECAUSE OF

00:21:01.230 --> 00:21:02.360
WHISKEY THAT WE NOW

00:21:02.360 --> 00:21:03.500
UNDERSTAND WHY THE GLACIERS

00:21:03.500 --> 00:21:04.600
WERE.

00:21:04.600 --> 00:21:09.300
(laughter)

00:21:13.400 --> 00:21:14.660
>> Narrator: LORIUS HAD THE

00:21:14.660 --> 00:21:15.660
IDEA THAT THE AIR TRAPPED IN

00:21:15.660 --> 00:21:16.930
THE ICE CONTAINED PRECIOUS

00:21:16.930 --> 00:21:21.360
INFORMATION.

00:21:24.230 --> 00:21:25.260
BUT IT WOULD BE YEARS BEFORE

00:21:25.260 --> 00:21:26.800
HE AND HIS TEAM COULD ANALYZE

00:21:26.800 --> 00:21:28.030
THE COMPOSITION OF THE GASES

00:21:28.030 --> 00:21:32.030
IN THE BUBBLES.

00:22:11.660 --> 00:22:12.260
>> Narrator: THE SNOW THAT

00:22:12.260 --> 00:22:13.400
FALLS PILES UP AND IS

00:22:13.400 --> 00:22:14.360
GRADUALLY TRANSFORMED

00:22:14.360 --> 00:22:15.900
INTO ICE.

00:22:15.900 --> 00:22:17.200
THE OLDEST ICE IS FOUND DEEP

00:22:17.200 --> 00:22:18.330
BELOW THE CENTRAL REGIONS OF

00:22:18.330 --> 00:22:21.260
ANTARCTICA.

00:22:21.260 --> 00:22:22.560
LORIUS KNEW THAT THEY HAD TO

00:22:22.560 --> 00:22:24.060
SEND SCIENTIFIC EXPEDITIONS

00:22:24.060 --> 00:22:25.700
TO THESE REMOTE REGIONS WHICH

00:22:25.700 --> 00:22:27.160
WERE THE MOST PROMISING, BUT

00:22:27.160 --> 00:22:32.130
ALSO THE HARDEST TO REACH.

00:22:32.130 --> 00:22:33.260
HE MOUNTED A NEW EXPEDITION

00:22:33.260 --> 00:22:35.300
TO TRY TO DRILL IN DOME C IN

00:22:35.300 --> 00:22:40.200
THE CENTER OF ANTARCTICA.

00:22:40.200 --> 00:22:41.430
THE EXPEDITION STARTED OUT,

00:22:41.430 --> 00:22:42.800
BUT PROGRESS WAS SLOWER THAN

00:22:42.800 --> 00:22:44.800
EXPECTED.

00:22:44.800 --> 00:22:45.860
THE VEHICLES, THOUGH

00:22:45.860 --> 00:22:46.960
IMPROVED, COULDN'T COPE WITH

00:22:46.960 --> 00:22:48.730
THE RUGGED TERRAIN.

00:22:48.730 --> 00:22:49.760
FUEL CONSUMPTION HAD BEEN

00:22:49.760 --> 00:22:51.300
UNDER ESTIMATED.

00:22:51.300 --> 00:22:52.230
THE SCIENTIFIC PROGRAM WAS

00:22:52.230 --> 00:22:56.360
TOO AMBITIOUS.

00:23:01.130 --> 00:23:02.300
IT BECAME APPARENT THAT THEY

00:23:02.300 --> 00:23:03.300
COULDN'T REACH THEIR GOAL

00:23:03.300 --> 00:23:04.400
BEFORE THE POLAR WINTER CUT

00:23:04.400 --> 00:23:07.530
OFF THEIR RETURN.

00:23:07.530 --> 00:23:13.260
THEY HAD TO TURN BACK.

00:23:13.960 --> 00:23:16.100
IT WAS THE START OF THE '70'S.

00:23:16.100 --> 00:23:17.230
LORIUS REFUSED TO ACCEPT

00:23:17.230 --> 00:23:19.500
DEFEAT.

00:23:19.500 --> 00:23:20.700
FOR THREE YEARS HE HAD BEEN

00:23:20.700 --> 00:23:22.130
SEARCHING FOR A WAY TO GET TO

00:23:22.130 --> 00:23:23.330
DOME C.

00:23:23.330 --> 00:23:24.560
IN THE END, IT WAS THE US

00:23:24.560 --> 00:23:25.930
NAVY WHO DROPPED HIM THERE BY

00:23:25.930 --> 00:23:27.960
PLANE.

00:24:40.360 --> 00:24:41.100
>> Narrator: THE SITE

00:24:41.100 --> 00:24:42.160
PROVED IDEAL.

00:24:42.160 --> 00:24:43.160
PRELIMINARY STUDIES WERE

00:24:43.160 --> 00:24:44.600
SUCCESSFUL.

00:24:44.600 --> 00:24:45.700
EVERYTHING WAS IN PLACE TO

00:24:45.700 --> 00:24:46.730
START DRILLING THE FOLLOWING

00:24:46.730 --> 00:24:49.530
YEAR.

00:24:57.100 --> 00:24:58.400
>> SOUTH POLE, THIS IS DOME

00:24:58.400 --> 00:25:00.460
CHARLIE, SOUTH POLE.

00:25:00.460 --> 00:25:01.530
>> Narrator: LORIUS ARRANGED

00:25:01.530 --> 00:25:02.760
FOR THE US NAVY PLANE THAT

00:25:02.760 --> 00:25:03.960
WAS TO COLLECT THEM TO BRING

00:25:03.960 --> 00:25:04.900
SOME OF THE NECESSARY

00:25:04.900 --> 00:25:06.500
MATERIALS, WHICH WOULD BE

00:25:06.500 --> 00:25:08.330
STORED ON-SITE, AWAITING THE

00:25:08.330 --> 00:25:12.400
FOLLOWING YEAR'S MISSION.

00:25:12.400 --> 00:25:13.430
THE EVACUATION OF THE TEAM

00:25:13.430 --> 00:25:17.430
COULD NOW START.

00:25:17.430 --> 00:25:25.930
(warning buzzer)

00:25:28.530 --> 00:25:32.930
THE PLANE FAILED TO TAKE OFF.

00:25:32.930 --> 00:25:33.700
FORTUNATELY THERE WERE NO

00:25:33.700 --> 00:25:35.200
CASUALTIES, BUT A SECOND

00:25:35.200 --> 00:25:40.130
PLANE STILL HAD TO BE SENT.

00:25:40.130 --> 00:25:48.660
(airplane engines)

00:25:54.600 --> 00:25:55.700
AFTER THIS NEW FAILURE THE

00:25:55.700 --> 00:25:57.900
SITUATION BECAME CRITICAL.

00:25:57.900 --> 00:25:59.630
THE US NAVY NOW HAD ONLY ONE

00:25:59.630 --> 00:26:00.830
PLANE LEFT CAPABLE OF LANDING

00:26:00.830 --> 00:26:02.660
ON THE SITE.

00:26:02.660 --> 00:26:04.930
IT WAS RUSHED TO THE SCENE.

00:26:04.930 --> 00:26:08.030
THIS WAS THEIR LAST CHANCE.

00:26:08.030 --> 00:26:22.930
(airplane engines)

00:26:22.930 --> 00:26:24.400
THE EVACUATION SUCCEEDED, BUT

00:26:24.400 --> 00:26:25.430
THE DRILLING PLANNED FOR THE

00:26:25.430 --> 00:26:28.130
FOLLOWING YEAR WAS CANCELLED.

00:26:28.130 --> 00:26:29.100
MEN COULD NOT BE TAKEN TO

00:26:29.100 --> 00:26:31.260
DOME C IF NO RESCUE PLANE WAS

00:26:31.260 --> 00:26:32.300
AVAILABLE SHOULD THE WORST

00:26:32.300 --> 00:26:36.800
HAPPEN.

00:26:39.930 --> 00:26:41.030
LORIUS SAW HIS RESEARCH

00:26:41.030 --> 00:26:43.500
STOPPED, HIS DREAM SHATTERED.

00:26:43.500 --> 00:26:45.560
IT WAS AN IMPASS.

00:27:47.430 --> 00:27:51.230
♪

00:27:51.230 --> 00:27:52.500
BUT LORIUS RECEIVED SOME

00:27:52.500 --> 00:27:54.630
UNEXPECTED SUPPORT.

00:27:54.630 --> 00:27:55.800
THE AMERICAN NATIONAL SCIENCE

00:27:55.800 --> 00:27:57.560
FOUNDATION DECIDED TO REPAIR

00:27:57.560 --> 00:28:00.500
THE DAMAGED PLANES ON-SITE.

00:28:00.500 --> 00:28:01.760
THREE YEARS, THREE SOUTHERN

00:28:01.760 --> 00:28:03.230
SUMMERS WOULD BE NEEDED TO

00:28:03.230 --> 00:28:05.160
COMPLETE THE REPAIRS.

00:28:05.160 --> 00:28:08.430
NOVEMBER 1977, 37,000 TONS OF

00:28:08.430 --> 00:28:09.430
MATERIALS WERE DELIVERED TO

00:28:09.430 --> 00:28:11.730
DOME C.

00:28:11.730 --> 00:28:12.600
THE DRILLING COULD BEGIN

00:28:12.600 --> 00:28:14.400
AT LAST.

00:28:14.400 --> 00:28:21.830
(machine noises)

00:28:21.830 --> 00:28:22.830
FOR LORIUS AND HIS TEAM IN

00:28:22.830 --> 00:28:24.200
GRENOBLE, THE DRILLING MARKED

00:28:24.200 --> 00:28:26.060
A TURNING POINT.

00:28:26.060 --> 00:28:27.860
ACCESS TO VERY OLD ICE,

00:28:27.860 --> 00:28:28.760
COMBINED WITH THE USE OF

00:28:28.760 --> 00:28:30.360
ISOTOPIC THERMOMETERS WAS

00:28:30.360 --> 00:28:31.360
GOING TO ENABLE THEM TO

00:28:31.360 --> 00:28:32.900
ESTABLISH TEMPERATURES FROM

00:28:32.900 --> 00:28:35.100
THOUSANDS OF YEARS AGO.

00:28:35.100 --> 00:28:36.100
LITTLE BY LITTLE, BY

00:28:36.100 --> 00:28:37.200
EXTRACTING THE ICE FROM DEEP

00:28:37.200 --> 00:28:38.800
DOWN, THEY WOULD BE ABLE TO

00:28:38.800 --> 00:28:40.100
CHART CLIMATE CHANGES OVER A

00:28:40.100 --> 00:28:41.430
PERIOD OF SEVERAL THOUSAND

00:28:41.430 --> 00:28:44.130
YEARS.

00:28:45.160 --> 00:28:46.430
AN ADDITIONAL DISCOVERY WOULD

00:28:46.430 --> 00:28:47.460
ALLOW THEM TO REFINE THEIR

00:28:47.460 --> 00:28:50.900
DATING.

00:28:56.030 --> 00:29:10.830
♪

00:29:43.160 --> 00:29:53.200
♪

00:29:53.200 --> 00:29:58.960
♪

00:30:34.230 --> 00:30:34.900
>> Narrator: BUT FRENCH

00:30:34.900 --> 00:30:36.030
RESOURCES AND TECHNIQUES

00:30:36.030 --> 00:30:36.900
WEREN'T UP TO DEEPER

00:30:36.900 --> 00:30:38.330
DRILLING.

00:30:38.330 --> 00:30:39.430
AT THAT TIME ONLY THE SOVIETS

00:30:39.430 --> 00:30:42.230
HAD THE NECESSARY EXPERIENCE.

00:30:42.230 --> 00:30:44.130
LORIUS KNEW THIS.

00:30:44.130 --> 00:30:45.260
HE VISITED THEIR BASE,

00:30:45.260 --> 00:30:46.900
VOSTOK, SITUATED AT AN

00:30:46.900 --> 00:30:49.760
ALTITUDE OF 3,600 METERS IN

00:30:49.760 --> 00:30:50.660
THE COLDEST PLACE ON

00:30:50.660 --> 00:30:53.700
THE EARTH.

00:30:57.300 --> 00:30:58.260
THIS IS THE HEIGHT OF THE

00:30:58.260 --> 00:30:59.800
COLD WAR.

00:30:59.800 --> 00:31:00.860
OFFICIALLY NO COOPERATION WAS

00:31:00.860 --> 00:31:02.030
POSSIBLE BETWEEN THE FRENCH

00:31:02.030 --> 00:31:05.800
AND THE SOVIET TEAMS.

00:31:05.800 --> 00:31:07.060
BUT THE GLACIOLOGISTS WORLD

00:31:07.060 --> 00:31:09.030
IS A SMALL ONE IN WHICH EVERY

00:31:09.030 --> 00:31:10.560
ONE IS A PIONEER AND SUPPORT

00:31:10.560 --> 00:31:12.760
IS ALWAYS GIVEN.

00:31:12.760 --> 00:31:13.660
LORIUS KNEW HIS SOVIET

00:31:13.660 --> 00:31:14.860
COUNTERPART, VLADIMIR

00:31:14.860 --> 00:31:16.600
KOTLYAKOV, DIRECTOR OF THE

00:31:16.600 --> 00:31:19.500
MOSCOW GEOGRAPHIC INSTITUTE.

00:32:54.200 --> 00:33:01.200
♪

00:33:01.200 --> 00:33:02.100
>> Narrator: MUCH MANEUVERING

00:33:02.100 --> 00:33:03.360
WAS REQUIRED ON THE PART OF

00:33:03.360 --> 00:33:04.800
CLAUDE LORIUS IN FRANCE AND

00:33:04.800 --> 00:33:06.000
VLADIMIR KOTLYAKOV IN THE

00:33:06.000 --> 00:33:08.030
SOVIET UNION.

00:33:08.030 --> 00:33:09.160
FINALLY, ON THE 31ST OF

00:33:09.160 --> 00:33:11.400
DECEMBER 1984, LORIUS AND HIS

00:33:11.400 --> 00:33:12.930
YOUNG COLLEAGUES ARRIVED AT

00:33:12.930 --> 00:33:14.560
THE VOSTOK STATION, JUST IN

00:33:14.560 --> 00:33:15.530
TIME FOR THE NEW YEAR

00:33:15.530 --> 00:33:18.030
CELEBRATIONS.

00:33:19.600 --> 00:33:21.000
AFTER SO MANY YEARS, LORIUS

00:33:21.000 --> 00:33:22.360
COULDN'T WAIT.

00:33:22.360 --> 00:33:23.630
THE NEXT DAY HE WENT TO WORK

00:33:23.630 --> 00:33:24.530
IN THE COLD ROOM BEFORE

00:33:24.530 --> 00:33:25.600
BREAKFAST AND GAVE AN

00:33:25.600 --> 00:33:26.760
ENTHUSIASTIC INTERVIEW TO

00:33:26.760 --> 00:33:29.000
RUSSIAN TV.

00:33:47.030 --> 00:33:57.060
♪

00:33:57.060 --> 00:34:41.260
♪

00:34:41.260 --> 00:34:41.930
>> Narrator: THE COLD ROOM

00:34:41.930 --> 00:34:42.930
CONTAINS ALL THE CORES

00:34:42.930 --> 00:34:44.000
ACCUMULATED HERE SINCE

00:34:44.000 --> 00:34:47.160
DRILLING BEGAN IN THE 1950'S.

00:34:47.160 --> 00:34:48.060
BUT THE RUSSIANS WERE ONLY

00:34:48.060 --> 00:34:49.060
TESTING OIL DRILLING

00:34:49.060 --> 00:34:50.100
TECHNIQUES.

00:34:50.100 --> 00:34:50.900
THEY HAD NO WAY OF

00:34:50.900 --> 00:34:53.430
ANALYZING ICE.

00:34:53.430 --> 00:34:54.700
IT WAS LORIUS' ISOTOPIC

00:34:54.700 --> 00:34:56.260
THERMOMETER AND HIS AIR

00:34:56.260 --> 00:34:57.730
BUBBLE ANALYSIS THAT ENABLED

00:34:57.730 --> 00:34:58.900
THE VOSTOK ICE TO TELL

00:34:58.900 --> 00:35:01.230
ITS STORY.

00:35:01.230 --> 00:35:02.300
RELAYS WERE ORGANIZED BETWEEN

00:35:02.300 --> 00:35:03.960
THE BASE AND GRENOBLE WHERE

00:35:03.960 --> 00:35:06.860
THE SAMPLES WERE ANALIZED.

00:35:06.860 --> 00:35:07.860
LORIUS USED THE TRIPS TO

00:35:07.860 --> 00:35:09.130
TRAIN A NEW GENERATION OF

00:35:09.130 --> 00:35:11.100
RESEARCHERS, ONE OF WHOM

00:35:11.100 --> 00:35:12.500
WOULD REPLACE HIM ON

00:35:12.500 --> 00:35:14.100
FUTURE EXPEDITIONS,

00:35:14.100 --> 00:35:18.300
JEAN-ROBERT PETIT.

00:37:15.030 --> 00:37:15.860
>> Narrator: IT WAS THEN THAT

00:37:15.860 --> 00:37:17.000
LORIUS REALIZED THAT THE

00:37:17.000 --> 00:37:18.100
EARTH'S CLIMATE WAS LESS

00:37:18.100 --> 00:37:19.330
STABLE THAN IT HAD BEEN

00:37:19.330 --> 00:37:21.660
THOUSANDS OF YEARS AGO.

00:37:21.660 --> 00:37:22.700
HIS INTUITION TOLD HIM THAT

00:37:22.700 --> 00:37:24.260
HUMAN ACTIVITY WAS CHANGING

00:37:24.260 --> 00:37:25.830
THE CLIMATE DUE TO CARBON

00:37:25.830 --> 00:37:27.900
DIOXIDE OMISSIONS, BUT AS

00:37:27.900 --> 00:37:30.100
YET, HE LACKED PROOF.

00:37:30.100 --> 00:37:30.960
HE HAD TO FIND A WAY TO

00:37:30.960 --> 00:37:32.160
RETURN TO VOSTOK TO

00:37:32.160 --> 00:37:35.500
CONSOLIDATE THE RESULTS,

00:37:35.500 --> 00:37:46.030
♪

00:37:46.030 --> 00:37:47.330
AT VOSTOK, HALF THE ICE CAP

00:37:47.330 --> 00:37:48.800
REMAINED TO BE DRILLED, A

00:37:48.800 --> 00:37:49.860
VERITABLE GOLD MINE FOR

00:37:49.860 --> 00:37:51.560
LORIUS.

00:37:51.560 --> 00:37:53.100
BUT THIS WAS 1991.

00:37:53.100 --> 00:37:54.230
THE COMMUNIST REGIME HAD

00:37:54.230 --> 00:37:55.630
COLLAPSED, AND WITH IT THE

00:37:55.630 --> 00:37:56.960
RESOURCES TO FINANCE THE

00:37:56.960 --> 00:37:58.330
POLAR BASE.

00:37:58.330 --> 00:37:59.360
THE DRILL OPERATORS WERE NO

00:37:59.360 --> 00:38:00.500
LONGER BEING PAID BY THEIR

00:38:00.500 --> 00:38:01.830
ADMINISTRATION.

00:38:01.830 --> 00:38:04.130
VOSTOK WAS ABOUT TO CLOSE.

00:38:57.830 --> 00:38:58.700
>> Narrator: RUSSIA SLOWLY

00:38:58.700 --> 00:39:00.160
REORGANIZED ITSELF.

00:39:00.160 --> 00:39:01.800
ECONOMIC ACTIVITY PICKED UP.

00:39:01.800 --> 00:39:02.960
THE ADMINISTRATION WAS

00:39:02.960 --> 00:39:04.160
REBUILT AND WAS ABLE TO PAY

00:39:04.160 --> 00:39:09.100
THE DRILL OPERATORS AGAIN.

00:39:09.100 --> 00:39:10.500
LORIUS TURNED 60.

00:39:10.500 --> 00:39:11.600
HE REMAINED IN OVER ALL

00:39:11.600 --> 00:39:13.030
CONTROL OF OPERATIONS BUT NO

00:39:13.030 --> 00:39:14.900
LONGER TRAVELED TO THE BASE.

00:39:14.900 --> 00:39:15.960
JEAN-ROBERT PETIT TOOK HIS

00:39:15.960 --> 00:39:17.830
PLACE ON-SITE.

00:39:54.260 --> 00:39:55.000
>> Narrator: THE LACK OF

00:39:55.000 --> 00:39:56.200
RESOURCES ON-SITE CONTINUED

00:39:56.200 --> 00:39:57.700
TO BE FELT.

00:39:57.700 --> 00:39:58.700
THEY HAD TO MAKE DUE WITH

00:39:58.700 --> 00:39:59.960
NEXT TO NOTHING, SOMETHING

00:39:59.960 --> 00:40:00.960
THE RUSSIAN TECHNICIANS WERE

00:40:00.960 --> 00:40:02.930
PARTICULARLY GOOD AT.

00:40:02.930 --> 00:40:04.160
AS BOTH HANDYMEN AND HIGHLY

00:40:04.160 --> 00:40:05.500
TRAINED ENGINEERS, THEY

00:40:05.500 --> 00:40:06.400
MANAGED TO REPAIR THEIR

00:40:06.400 --> 00:40:07.460
FREQUENT MECHANICAL

00:40:07.460 --> 00:40:08.600
BREAKDOWNS AND SOLVE THE

00:40:08.600 --> 00:40:09.900
TECHNICAL PROBLEMS POSED BY A

00:40:09.900 --> 00:40:11.430
DRILL HOLE THREE THOUSAND

00:40:11.430 --> 00:40:13.600
METERS DEEP.

00:40:37.260 --> 00:40:46.960
♪

00:40:46.960 --> 00:40:47.900
>> Narrator: IN GRENOBLE,

00:40:47.900 --> 00:40:50.230
LORIUS, REYNAUD, JOUZEL,

00:40:50.230 --> 00:40:51.660
PETIT, AND A NEW GENERATION

00:40:51.660 --> 00:40:53.100
OF RESEARCHERS CONTINUED

00:40:53.100 --> 00:40:57.360
THEIR STUDY OF PAST CLIMATES.

00:40:57.360 --> 00:40:58.600
THEY'D SOON RECONSTRUCT THE

00:40:58.600 --> 00:40:59.600
CLIMATE OVER THE LAST

00:40:59.600 --> 00:41:02.500
400,000 YEARS.

00:41:02.500 --> 00:41:12.530
♪

00:41:12.530 --> 00:41:31.530
♪

00:41:31.530 --> 00:41:33.500
400,000 YEARS REPRESENTS FOUR

00:41:33.500 --> 00:41:34.860
CLIMATIC CYCLES BETWEEN

00:41:34.860 --> 00:41:36.330
GLACIAL AND INTER-GLACIAL

00:41:36.330 --> 00:41:38.100
PERIODS.

00:41:38.100 --> 00:41:39.000
THE EVIDENCE CONFIRMED THE

00:41:39.000 --> 00:41:40.230
REGULARITIES AS WELL AS THE

00:41:40.230 --> 00:41:41.830
EXCEPTIONS.

00:41:41.830 --> 00:41:42.860
THIS WAS THE PROOF THEY

00:41:42.860 --> 00:41:44.430
NEEDED.

00:41:44.430 --> 00:41:45.500
LORIUS' TEAM COULD SHOW WITH

00:41:45.500 --> 00:41:46.900
CERTAINTY THAT FOR THE FIRST

00:41:46.900 --> 00:41:48.600
TIME IN CLIMATE HISTORY THE

00:41:48.600 --> 00:41:49.830
REGULAR OSCILATION IN

00:41:49.830 --> 00:41:52.800
TEMPERATURE HAD BEEN BROKEN.

00:43:57.360 --> 00:44:05.130
(footsteps in snow)

00:44:05.130 --> 00:44:05.900
>> Narrator: IN ORDER TO

00:44:05.900 --> 00:44:07.130
DEEPEN OUR UNDERSTANDING OF

00:44:07.130 --> 00:44:08.400
THE CLIMATIC MACHINE, AND

00:44:08.400 --> 00:44:09.400
THUS CONVINCE THE

00:44:09.400 --> 00:44:10.860
POLITICIANS, LORIUS BELIEVES

00:44:10.860 --> 00:44:13.760
THE RESEARCH MUST CONTINUE.

00:44:13.760 --> 00:44:15.260
ON THE EVE OF HIS RETIREMENT,

00:44:15.260 --> 00:44:16.400
LORIUS IS USING HIS

00:44:16.400 --> 00:44:17.730
REPUTATION, HIS SCIENTIFIC

00:44:17.730 --> 00:44:19.030
REWARDS, AND HIS NEW

00:44:19.030 --> 00:44:20.230
APPOINTMENT AS A MEMBER OF

00:44:20.230 --> 00:44:21.860
THE ACADMIE FRANCAISE TO

00:44:21.860 --> 00:44:22.960
ALLOW YOUNGER COLLEAGUES TO

00:44:22.960 --> 00:44:25.100
CONTINUE POLAR RESEARCH.

00:44:46.030 --> 00:44:57.060
♪

00:44:57.060 --> 00:44:57.860
>> Narrator: SEVERAL DRILL

00:44:57.860 --> 00:44:59.000
HOLES HAVE BEEN INITIATED IN

00:44:59.000 --> 00:45:00.560
ANTARCTICA.

00:45:00.560 --> 00:45:01.860
ONE OF THE MOST SPECTACULAR

00:45:01.860 --> 00:45:03.730
IS AT DOME C WHERE 30 YEARS

00:45:03.730 --> 00:45:05.100
EARLIER LORIUS SANK HIS

00:45:05.100 --> 00:45:08.030
FIRST HOLE.

00:45:08.030 --> 00:45:11.100
THIS IS THE EPICA PROJECT.

00:45:11.100 --> 00:45:19.960
♪

